# Checkmk Docker Setup

This repository provides a simple and efficient way to deploy Checkmk using Docker and Docker Compose. Checkmk is a comprehensive IT monitoring system that helps you monitor all aspects of your infrastructure, including networks, servers, cloud environments, databases, and applications.

## Table of Contents

- [Checkmk Docker Setup](#checkmk-docker-setup)
  - [Table of Contents](#table-of-contents)
  - [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)
  - [Installation](#installation)

## Prerequisites

Before you begin, ensure you have the following software installed on your local machine:

- [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/)
- [Docker Compose](https://docs.docker.com/compose/install/)

## Installation

1. Clone this repository to your local machine:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/checkmk-docker-setup.git
   cd checkmk-docker-setup
